    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `Bun.INI`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**9 files** touch points across 4 layers:\n\n### Layer 1 — Core Parser (new)\n- **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** *(new)*: Self-contained line-by-line INI parser producing a `bun.ast.Expr` AST. Handles `[sections]`→nested objects, `key=value` pairs, `;`/`#` comments, bare keys→`true`, coerces `true`/`false`/`null`, strips inline comments.\n\n### Layer 2 — JS Bindings (new)\n- **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** *(new)*: `parse` follows the TOMLObject pattern (→ `printJSON` → `toJSByParseJSON`). `stringify` walks the JSValue tree producing section headers for objects and `key=value`/`key[]=val` for primitives/arrays.\n\n### Layer 3 — Registration (4 files modified)\n- **`src/interchange.zig`**: +1 line to export the `ini` module\n- **`src/bun.js/api.zig`**: +1 line to export `INIObject`\n- **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`**: 4 changes — lazy property constant, `@export` call, getter function, import constant\n- **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`**: add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n- **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`**: add row to property table\n\n### Layer 4 — Types & Tests\n- **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`**: `namespace INI { parse(input: string): object; stringify(input: object): string; }`\n- **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** *(new)*: parse + stringify tests covering sections, comments, coercion, round-trips",
